Miranda T. C. Curtis: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 28, 2017 10:55 AM ET
Diversified Telecommunication Services

Company Overview of United International Holdings, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Miranda T. C. Curtis  President of Liberty Global Japan, United International Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships61--
Background

		Ms. Miranda T. C. Curtis served as the President at Liberty Global Japan Division at Liberty Global plc and United International Holdings, Inc. from June 2005 to April 2010. Ms. Curtis served as a Senior Vice President of Liberty Media Corporation. She served as a Senior Vice President of Liberty Global plc from March 2004 to June 2005. She served as President of Liberty Media International Holdings LLC (LMINT), a subsidiary of Liberty Media International Inc., from ... February 1999 to June 2004. She served as an Executive Vice President of LMI from September 1996 to February 1999. She has worked with the Liberty group since 1988 and has built and managed international joint ventures on the Liberty group's behalf across Europe and Asia-Pacific. She served as the Senior Director of J:COM. From May 1992 to August 1996, she served in senior management positions for LMI. She worked in the UK cable industry with the predecessors of Telewest and Flextech and in the BBC's commercial division. Ms. Curtis has substantial experience of the international consumer and technology sectors and extensive knowledge of the global broadband cable industry. In her 20-year career with Liberty, she led its investments in digital distribution and content operations across Continental Europe and Asia-Pacific, most notably in Japan, where she led the creation and development of the Jupiter Telecommunications group of companies. Ms. Curtis served as Executive Vice President of Tele-Communications International, Inc. since September 1996, Senior Vice President from May 1995 to August 1996 and Vice President from October 1994 to May 1995. She served as an Officer of several of Tele Communications International Inc.'s subsidiaries. She has experience in building multinational leadership teams, the negotiation and oversight of international joint ventures and cross-border deal making. She serves as Chairman of Waterstone's. She serves as Deputy Chairman of Garsington Opera Limited and The Royal Shakespeare Company. Ms. Curtis has been an Independent Director of Liberty Global plc since June 2010. She has been an Independent Non-Executive Director of Marks and Spencer Group plc since February 3, 2012. She has been Lead Non-Executive Director and Non-Executive Director of Foreign And Commonwealth Office (U.K.) since April 6, 2017. She serves as a Director of Jupiter Programming Co. Ltd., MultiThematiques S.A. and Princes Holding Limited. She serves as Director of Encore International Inc. She serves as Director of The Royal Shakespeare Company. She has served on a number of private and public company boards across Asia and Europe. She is on the Board of Governors of the Institute for Government. She served as a Non-Executive Director of Telewest Global Inc. since September 1998. She served as Director of Jupiter Telecommunications Co. Ltd. She served as a Director of National Express Group plc from June 1, 2008 to May 10, 2012. From May 1992 to October 1994, Ms. Curtis served as a Director of International Development in the international division of Tele-Communications Inc. (TCI) and was principally responsible for that division's activities in Asia and the United Kingdom. She serves as Chair of the leading African education charity Camfed. Since October 2011, she has been Chairman of Waterstones. Ms. Curtis studied in London Business School and holds a Honours Degree in Spanish from University of Durham.Read Full Background




